  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/gaming/\" rel=\"tag\">游戏产品</a>, <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/industry/\" rel=\"tag\">产业新闻</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/02/07/blizzard-to-fund-competitive-gaming-at-the-college-level/\"><img alt=\"Game tournament at BlizzCon 2010\" src=\"http://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/adam/90439a29f6e78089b1976fbdf1480bf5/warcraft-tournament-glenn-batuyong-flickr.jpg\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n电子竞技的世界中大多都是年轻的面孔，其中又以大学生居多，而这样的身份，在真正筹划比赛时多少会有些力不从心。面对这样的情况，游戏巨头<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/tag/blizzard\">暴雪</a>决定出来帮他们一把。据悉他们未来会为 TeSPA（The eSports Association 电子竞技运动协会）旗下的大学游戏团体提供帮助，随着团体规模的增大，Blizzard 会拿出更多的资金、比赛奖励和宣传用品（团体人数超过 200 人后甚至还有望青睐特别嘉宾）。当然，这么做的最终目的肯定是为了卖出更多的游戏，但若能同时帮助电竞圈良性发展的话，何乐而不为呢？<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/02/07/blizzard-to-fund-competitive-gaming-at-the-college-level/\">Engadget</a>、<span class=\"via\"><a href=\"http://www.dailydot.com/esports/blizzard-esports-tespa-partnership/\" target=\"_blank\">The Daily Dot</a></span><br />\n引用来源：<span class=\"source\"><a href=\"http://investor.activision.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=824191\" target=\"_blank\">Activision</a></span>、<span class=\"source\"><a href=\"http://tespa.org/benefits/\" target=\"_blank\">TeSPA</a></span></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/02/07/blizzard-to-fund-competitive-gaming-at-the-college-level/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20825542/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/02/07/blizzard-to-fund-competitive-gaming-at-the-college-level/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
